## Description {#details}

<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/pdb/pdbsymbolcustom">PDBSymbolCustom</a> represents symbols that are compiler-specific and do not fit anywhere else in the lexical hierarchy.

<a href="https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/d88sf09h.aspx">https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/d88sf09h.aspx</a>

## Public Member Functions

### dump() {#a1bb278320c0b0b7363d9c1feface10b9}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>void PDBSymbolCustom::dump (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/pdb/pdbsymdumper">PDBSymDumper</a> &amp; Dumper) const</>}
  labels = {["virtual"]}>
Dumps the contents of a symbol a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/raw-ostream">raw&#95;ostream</a>.

By default this will just call <a href="#a1bb278320c0b0b7363d9c1feface10b9">dump()</a> on the underlying RawSymbol, which allows us to discover unknown properties, but individual implementations of <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/pdb/pdbsymbol">PDBSymbol</a> may override the behavior to only dump known fields.
